author: Anonymous Helix
title: Autograder Explanation- Additional Tests
question:
Hi, I noticed that in the autograder explanations the very last sentence for the additional tests section is cutoff, it says,
"This indicates a situation where the submitted problem set has a self-consistent design for not quite"
I was wondering what it was supposed to say since I'm working on the problem set and my tests are all valid and passing, but I keep having an additional test fail,  thanks in advance!
student_answer:
This might be because there is something wrong with your code, that when the autograder ran a test, it failed. So I advise you look over your code again.
Edit: Just adding acknowledement that the autograder explanation is intended to help understand what part of the code to revisit, and the explanation seems to have a truncated sentence.  Not sure what the end of that sentence originally was, so you might just have to get creative with troubleshooting your code.  It's good practice, at least!
